description.plain:
Denzel Rae Don Curry, formally known as Denzel Curry, was born in Carol City, Florida on February 16, 1995. He is of Bahamian and Native American descent.

He started rapping in 6th grade and frequently challenged others to rap battles at a local Boys & Girls club. He attended Miami’s Design And Architecture High School for his first two years of high school before being expelled. He went on to attend Carol City High School while he worked on what would become his debut album, Nostalgic 64.

Throughout 2011-2012, he posted various amateur mixtapes on SoundCloud and DatPiff such as King Remembered in 2011 and Strictly For my R.V.I.D.X.R.Z in 2012, which grabbed the attention of Earl Sweatshirt.

Not long after the group disbanded, he joined SpaceGhostPurrp’s group Raider Klan. After several disagreements between Purrp and Denzel, he would leave the group and, simultaneously, start his solo rap career, alongside the release of his SpaceGhostPurrp’s 2016 diss-track, “PURRPOSELY.”

His debut album Nostalgic 64 was released in September 2013, and was followed by a double-sided EP in June 2015 titled 32 Zel/Planet Shrooms, which included the gold-certified and breakout hit single, “ULTIMATE.”

His last release before a hiatus was his second studio album/mixtape hybrid, Imperial, which was released in March 2016.

On July 17, Denzel released his critically acclaimed third studio album, TA13OO, which was divided into three acts, released period 3 days of the complete album: “Light,” released on July 15; “Gray,” released on July 16; and “Dark,” released on July 17, alongside the entire album — After its release, it became his first charting album worldwide, peaking at #28 on the Billboard 200, and received generally positive reviews.

Almost a year after releasing the project, on May 31, 2019, Curry dropped his fourth studio album, ZUU, dedicated to his life in Carol City and inspired by the Miami culture, including features from Rick Ross, Kiddo Marv, Sam Sneak or Ice Billion Berg, the album has two supporting singles, his gold-certified single “RICKY” and “SPEEDBOAT.”

On February 7, 2020, Denzel would team up with his frequent collaborator and friend, Kenny Beats to release their collaborative 8-track project, UNLOCKED, and exactly one year later, on March 5, 2021, UNLOCKED 1.5, a re-edition of the project was released.

Nearly three years later after his latest album, on March 25, 2022, Denzel release what would be his evolution musically than he usually has with his fifth studio album, Melt My Eyez, See Your Future — The 14-track album would have 3 promotional singles during its rollout: “Walkin,” “Zatoichi” with slowthai, and “Troubles” with veteran rapper T-Pain.

songs.title: ULTIMATE

description.plain:
“ULTIMATE” is the breakout hit by Florida rapper Denzel Curry. It became popular in 2016 thanks to a video meme that uses the song’s high-intensity hook to punctuate any unexpectedly “savage” moment:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1Qv2mtyLwA0

The song marks the climax of aggression on Denzel Curry’s double EP 32 Zel/Planet Shrooms. Ronny J’s chaotic production paired with Curry’s unique brand of wordplay come together for a banger that only gets more relentless as Curry’s vocals intensify in the second verse.

When asked about the song’s adoption by viral memes, Denzel said:

I made this a year ago. And to see what it did now is funny as hell, cause its like, damn, this been out, but people just now catching on to it. People feel like they’re ultimate. I feel like its a blessing that all this is happening because its bringing more attention to myself and my music.

The use of the term “ULT/Ultimate” by Denzel Curry and his C9 crew seems to have originated from this song.

songs.full_title: CLOUT COBAIN | CLOUT CO13A1N by Denzel Curry
songs.title: CLOUT COBAIN | CLOUT CO13A1N

description.plain:
“CLOUT COBAIN | CLOUT CO13A1N” is directed at the destructive consequences which occur as a result of chasing popularity, as heavily suggested by the title. Denzel delivers this message on one hand, through the individual dealing with suicidal thoughts and paranoia. Secondly, through the people surrounding the individual, ready to sabotage and plot against them in order to acquire their own ‘clout’.

Aesthetically, the clothes Denzel is wearing on the cover art and video are eerily similar to Kurt Cobain’s prior to his death. Also, the ‘clout’ motif is an especially interesting note on modern internet culture, when considering Denzel’s link to Kurt Cobain’s infamous sunglasses, who Denzel himself had dubbed “Clout Goggles.”

songs.title: (RIP YAMS) SPACEGHOSTPUSSY
songs.title_with_featured: (RIP YAMS) SPACEGHOSTPUSSY (Ft. Lofty305, Ski Mask the Slump God & XXXTENTACION)

description.plain:
Built off of guttural deliveries and hard-hitting production, “SPACEGHOSTPUSSY (RIP YAMS)” is Denzel Curry’s iconic first diss track towards former friend and Raider Klan mentor SpaceGhostPurrp. The song was written in reaction to SpaceGhostPurrp’s infamous series of disrespectful tweets about A$AP Yams’s death from drug overdose on January 18, 2015. According to Curry, he originally wouldn’t want to react to the offensive comments Purrp made towards him since his departure from the the Raider Klan in 2013, but had to retaliate following Purrp’s comments on Yams' death.

The song features four of Curry’s “ULT House”’s then-residents, XXXTENTACION, Ski Mask the Slump God, Lofty305 and Ronny J. Denzel explained in a January 2018 interview with Montreality that the song was written after a soccer game on the first day that he actually got to know X and Ski.

Two days later, Curry and XXX released the follow-up to “SPACEGHOSTPUSSY (RIP YAMS),” “Purrposely”. SpaceGhostPurrp would retaliate on the same day with “TRAINING DAY END OF DENZEL CURRY” before Denzel proclaimed in a tweet that he had “won” and that he wouldn’t release any more diss songs towards Purrp. X released his third diss to Purrp, “#ImSippinTeainYoHood,” a month later.
